abstract: Solicitor General Elena Kagan is on Capitol Hill again today for her second round of meetings with senators. Meanwhile, President Obama travels to New York to speak about the economy and attend a fund-raoser.
snippet: Solicitor General Elena Kagan is on Capitol Hill again today for her second round of meetings with senators. Meanwhile, President Obama travels to New York to speak about the economy and attend a fund-raoser.
lead_paragraph: Solicitor General Elena Kagan is on Capitol Hill again today for her second round of meetings with the senators who will decide whether she joins the Supreme Court.

abstract: In a setback for Senator Christopher J. Dodd, the Senate voted to amend its financial regulatory legislation to allow the Federal Reserve to retain its supervision of state-chartered banks and some bank-holding companies.
snippet: In a setback for Senator Christopher J. Dodd, the Senate voted to amend its financial regulatory legislation to allow the Federal Reserve to retain its supervision of state-chartered banks and some bank-holding companies.
lead_paragraph: The Senate on Wednesday voted to amend its major financial regulatory legislation to allow the Federal Reserve to retain its supervision of state-chartered banks and bank-holding companies with less than $50 billion in assets rather than transfer that supervisory authority to the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation.
headline_main: Senate Backs Fed Oversight of State Banks
